Manchester City beat Leeds 4-0 in
the fifth round of Englandâ€™s F.A. Cup and Chelsea defeated
Brentford by the same score in a fourth-round replay. Wigan
overcame Huddersfield 4-1 as all three Premier League teams won.  Sergio Aguero  scored twice for league champion City, with
 Yaya Toure  and  Carlos Tevez  also getting goals against second-
tier Leeds at the Etihad Stadium.  Cup-holder Chelsea beat third-tier Brentford with second-
half goals by  Juan Mata , Oscar,  Frank Lampard  and captain John
Terry at Stamford Bridge. The Blues will play at Middlesbrough
in the fifth round.  Arouna Kone scored twice as Premier League Wigan eased
past second-tier Huddersfield in a fifth-round match. Callum
McManaman and James McArthur also scored for the Latics.  Yesterday, second-tier Blackburn upset Arsenal 1-0.
Millwall won 3-0 at non-league Luton, Barnsley won 3-1 at MK
Dons and third-division Oldham drew 2-2 with Everton. Manchester
United hosts Reading tomorrow.  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
